255
00:46:25,040 --> 00:46:26,880
Nine... Ten...

256
00:49:15,640 --> 00:49:17,960
They've taken everybody

257
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:21,000
Who can fight such a war?

258
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:25,680
Not against army but against innocent people

259
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:32,960
people will be dieing in those camps and compounds

260
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:38,480
people will be dieing without food, without any choice

261
00:49:40,680 --> 00:49:44,920
or was it my fault?
indirect choice?

262
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:57,040
look what they did

263
00:50:32,520 --> 00:50:39,560
[ raised the sky up and set the balance of all things ]

264
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,680
Its the Omar

265
00:52:58,160 --> 00:52:59,280
No

266
00:52:59,680 --> 00:53:01,600
We will be massacred

267
00:53:06,040 --> 00:53:08,040
you have a chance to get away
Take it

268
00:53:08,080 --> 00:53:09,640
Go with this mare
Don't think of it

269
00:53:14,040 --> 00:53:16,160
Go... Go...

270
00:53:44,240 --> 00:53:45,440
Ali

271
00:53:46,640 --> 00:53:47,560
Ali

272
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,680
Up behing me
Up behind me

273
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:37,320
Go back.. Go back for that boy

274
00:54:37,720 --> 00:54:40,360
The horse won't take too
His mare knows that

275
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:48,000
Hurry up Ustad Omar

276
00:56:38,640 --> 00:56:41,200
So, you are the brave young man

277
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:45,880
The brave young man who saved Muktar from me

278
00:56:52,560 --> 00:56:56,280
why did you do it?
you are young

279
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:59,920
you had your whole life behind it

280
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:05,800
Tell me
Would you want to live?

281
00:57:05,840 --> 00:57:06,560
come on

282
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:09,840
I want him to live more

283
00:57:10,280 --> 00:57:12,560
You will make a fine soldier

284
00:57:13,880 --> 00:57:18,720
Would you think of joining us?
You earn more with us lion prince

285
00:57:24,960 --> 00:57:26,680
you will corrupt him

286
00:57:27,280 --> 00:57:30,440
Get him out of here
Give him Riyals, fruit, honey.. whatever

287
00:57:31,320 --> 00:57:35,760
Don't harm him
Hang him..
in the morning

288
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:48,720
Desert is their home, General
I'd be careful.. next

289
00:57:49,320 --> 00:57:54,160
You may be next to him, even if its a small paragraph in a newspaper in Rome

290
00:57:55,080 --> 00:58:01,920
You touch my strength Prince

291
00:58:02,880 --> 00:58:06,000
A gain in the mind of Rome

292
00:58:06,400 --> 00:58:10,560
is more important to me than the generation of men of Libia

293
00:58:12,720 --> 00:58:16,320
And what happens if you are... you are forgotten in Rome and

294
00:58:16,880 --> 00:58:19,280
you are remembered in Libia?

295
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:24,560
Why do you worry so much about that?
you see, we will write the history
Libia is our crown of thorns

296
00:58:34,280 --> 00:58:37,120
Libia is our career

297
00:58:38,160 --> 00:58:39,320
locate it

298
00:58:42,960 --> 00:58:45,120
locate it

299
00:58:49,040 --> 00:58:53,320
Its always the same
We can never persue them in the desert

300
00:58:54,240 --> 00:58:57,800
I must conquer the desert as much on a crusade

301
00:58:59,680 --> 00:59:03,560
from here to here
Simple.. isn't it?

302
00:59:04,560 --> 00:59:06,320
No, its not

303
00:59:06,360 --> 00:59:08,040
But, its only empty desert

304
00:59:08,080 --> 00:59:12,120
There's nothing there, just wind and sand,

305
00:59:14,680 --> 00:59:15,520
not even much opposition

306
00:59:16,400 --> 00:59:20,360
what can you get from it?
worry for Rome

307
00:59:20,920 --> 00:59:25,800
an extension of the Emperor and finding the revolution to the mountain

308
00:59:27,040 --> 00:59:32,680
my name, a new page in military history

309
00:59:33,040 --> 00:59:36,160
seize it as quiteful as offense

310
00:59:38,720 --> 00:59:40,920
I will surprise you

311
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,040
come in

312
00:59:49,440 --> 00:59:53,200
Diatich, now is your time. Please sit down

313
00:59:57,400 --> 01:00:01,080
The man who can make peace with a hand-shake

314
01:00:04,080 --> 01:00:07,560
Do it now....

315
01:00:07,600 --> 01:00:10,000
Hands across the desert

316
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:13,720
I wish to instigate peace talks with his excelleny

317
01:00:17,240 --> 01:00:20,680
Omar Muktar

318
01:00:24,080 --> 01:00:28,440
That will not be so easy now.
Now, you will do it, won't you?

319
01:00:28,840 --> 01:00:33,440
And what are the pre-conditions for talks with Omar Muktar?

320
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:39,360
No pre-conditions. The whole of Libia is open to discussion. Look at it

321
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:39,840
Look at it

322
01:00:42,080 --> 01:00:46,040
We go to the conference table with no pre-mind or not

323
01:00:46,880 --> 01:00:52,000
He fought us for 20 years.
We are anamoly, he knows

324
01:00:52,320 --> 01:00:54,960
He'll sack all our promises

325
01:00:55,200 --> 01:00:59,880
20 years is too long. I mean can you imagine escaping hanging for 20 years and you can't win just hoping to keep on

326
01:00:59,880 --> 01:01:02,280
Its a war. It's a hope man would be mad

327
01:01:02,400 --> 01:01:06,880
to get on his high horse to back false promises.

328
01:01:09,720 --> 01:01:13,800
When may I... your excellency's man sit down with him?

329
01:01:18,760 --> 01:01:22,960
When you talk to Omar Muktar, it must be with the speed of the tesh

330
01:01:24,400 --> 01:01:28,760
Regress whether you are talk or not. Interest in your tie-in

331
01:01:34,480 --> 01:01:38,360
Yes, I will try

332
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:39,360
Thank you very much

333
01:01:40,360 --> 01:01:44,160
Thank you for coming at very short notice
It was very kind of you

334
01:01:50,120 --> 01:01:51,040
Thank you

335
01:01:56,480 --> 01:02:00,200
Well, let us settle this.
Duditch is not the right man.

336
01:02:00,840 --> 01:02:03,720
He will offer. But Muktar can't take

337
01:02:04,040 --> 01:02:06,960
and Muktar will ask what he can't give

338
01:02:07,560 --> 01:02:11,440
which makes me think, you want things go long

339
01:02:15,600 --> 01:02:16,880
No

340
01:02:17,560 --> 01:02:22,280
I want some fair chance, I want some peace course

341
01:02:22,320 --> 01:02:23,040
I want to win that peace

342
01:02:23,240 --> 01:02:28,920
But sometimes Prince when you are strong, it means natural conquest is not enough

343
01:02:30,680 --> 01:02:35,440
He won't give me peace
But he will give me time

344
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:36,840
what I need is time

345
01:03:05,200 --> 01:03:07,640
So, thats what he looks like

346
01:03:08,200 --> 01:03:13,040
After all these years, we are the first to see him

347
01:03:17,080 --> 01:03:19,560
The Old Lion!

348
01:03:30,320 --> 01:03:31,800
Colonel Duditchi?
yes sir

349
01:03:36,480 --> 01:03:37,400
Please

350
01:03:42,640 --> 01:03:45,440
This side

351
01:04:00,480 --> 01:04:04,680
Curnel Barilo, military Governor of Merch!

352
01:04:06,120 --> 01:04:12,680
This is Commissionor Roberto, has come directly from Rome for advice and assistance

353
01:04:18,080 --> 01:04:20,760
You invited us here to talk

354
01:04:21,480 --> 01:04:22,560
We are here

355
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:29,280
You Excellency,
it is my one wish

356
01:04:29,680 --> 01:04:33,760
to see the Italian and the Arab together in the Solopian desert

357
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:41,640
I could see a future of common cause, give and take of character skill,

358
01:04:42,640 --> 01:04:47,080
our civilization and your culture

359
01:04:47,760 --> 01:04:49,280
in marriage of virtues

360
01:04:50,000 --> 01:04:54,360
I want observators to come from Tunisia or Egypt

361
01:04:54,720 --> 01:04:57,560
to witness any agreements between us

362
01:04:59,120 --> 01:05:00,960
... as for as I am concerned

363
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:01,720
Out of the question Duditch

364
01:05:02,400 --> 01:05:07,040
He is seeking International Recognition, as if the Beduins were an independent nation which they are not

365
01:05:07,440 --> 01:05:11,400
They are subjects within our province

366
01:05:12,120 --> 01:05:15,560
Our arguments are not within nations, but between Italians

367
01:05:15,960 --> 01:05:19,880
We cannot permit outside interference in our internal affairs

368
01:05:20,360 --> 01:05:24,520
They why must you represent this. We are not Italians, and do not tell us who we are

369
01:05:26,160 --> 01:05:29,920
We were born where we were born only by the will of God

370
01:05:30,280 --> 01:05:32,880
and only by our own mothers. We are not you

371
01:05:33,680 --> 01:05:37,680
And who will come as Foreign Observators later uh?

372
01:05:37,680 --> 01:05:39,280
As yet, nothing written, nothing witnessed

373
01:05:41,080 --> 01:05:43,560
But, we have written

374
01:05:59,440 --> 01:06:03,160
You must have muslime schools..
Oh, yes

375
01:06:03,640 --> 01:06:07,600
no question. Freedom of education, no question

376
01:06:08,440 --> 01:06:10,680
The schools will be re-opened

377
01:06:13,000 --> 01:06:17,000
We must have some form of national protection

378
01:06:17,760 --> 01:06:22,960
We must have our National Parliament..
Your Parliament is a matter for Rome

379
01:06:22,960 --> 01:06:24,440
This tent is not the place

380
01:06:24,440 --> 01:06:27,640
Why not?
You pitched it, no conditions you said, no limits, no conclusions,

381
01:06:28,280 --> 01:06:32,320
everything open on this table in this tent

382
01:06:33,000 --> 01:06:38,440
Let us say that, at present we will note your demand for the parliament

383
01:06:38,600 --> 01:06:39,720
Mark it well

384
01:06:46,200 --> 01:06:52,080
The confiscated lands must be given back

385
01:06:52,880 --> 01:06:53,960
well...

386
01:06:54,000 --> 01:06:58,040
I wouldn't say confiscated lands

387
01:06:58,520 --> 01:07:02,840
I would say lands reserved for settlement and cultivation, lands to be developed

388
01:07:03,480 --> 01:07:09,320
To be developed by Italians?

389
01:07:10,000 --> 01:07:15,520
I tell you there is no space 20 years.
For years, the land would be packed with people

390
01:07:16,400 --> 01:07:22,000
Why do you think we fight you?
But, the new settlements will provide employment

391
01:07:23,080 --> 01:07:26,920
as long as you take our lands, as long as where I was born, we must fight you

392
01:07:27,600 --> 01:07:29,680
must?
yes, we must

393
01:07:30,040 --> 01:07:37,360
But, I have it on religious authority that your Quran does not allow you to fight a war you cannot win

394
01:07:37,960 --> 01:07:41,440
Now, you are going to interpret our religion first...

395
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:47,080
The Book leaves no doubt.
It is our duty to God to defend ourselves

396
01:07:47,440 --> 01:07:51,520
against those who have driven us out of our homes

397
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:58,040
I think this might be a good time to adjourn
We are in no hurry

398
01:08:00,600 --> 01:08:03,040
why are you delaying?

399
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:09,320
Your excellency, we are obliged to refer your demands to Rome

400
01:08:09,880 --> 01:08:15,480
On 3rd, the next meeting, we will give you their answer and make our proposal

401
01:08:17,560 --> 01:08:23,360
Atleast.. Atleast we know that we all want the blood-shed between us to end

402
01:09:40,320 --> 01:09:43,280
An Italian Invasion...

403
01:09:44,120 --> 01:09:47,120
The first use of aircraft in combat,

404
01:09:47,520 --> 01:09:50,600
the first Portekts of the desert

405
01:09:51,120 --> 01:09:54,000
history will mark that gentlemen

406
01:09:57,440 --> 01:10:01,760
What we need was time.
Now, we have achieved that time

407
01:10:02,680 --> 01:10:06,760
with talk peace
with a lot of weapons

408
01:10:08,160 --> 01:10:12,080
1. Omar Muktar's men will come under the command of Italian Officer

409
01:10:13,600 --> 01:10:14,960
Go on...

410
01:10:16,120 --> 01:10:19,880
2. The Italian Government will pay monthly salary to these men

411
01:10:20,600 --> 01:10:21,760
Go on

412
01:10:22,600 --> 01:10:23,560
Go on...

413
01:10:25,560 --> 01:10:31,160
The Government reserves the right to punish any persons who committed a crime before this agreement

414
01:10:32,000 --> 01:10:35,360
Omar Muktar will have no right to protect such persons

415
01:10:36,520 --> 01:10:40,440
4.
These terms mean dis-honour
Absolute surrender

416
01:10:40,920 --> 01:10:43,760
That even subjects for discussion

417
01:10:44,400 --> 01:10:50,160
The Italian Government undertakes to pay Omar Muktar a pension of 50,000 Lirahs a month

418
01:10:50,520 --> 01:10:53,240
and to provide him with a comfortable house

419
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:57,640
Do I deserve so much?

420
01:10:58,040 --> 01:11:02,200
I've been so successful to offer me 50,000 Lirahs a month?

421
01:11:03,880 --> 01:11:08,400
You know, by offering me bribes, you are insulting me

422
01:11:09,040 --> 01:11:13,840
Your excellency,
I made that proposal

423
01:11:14,800 --> 01:11:15,800
Believe me..

424
01:11:16,080 --> 01:11:20,120
It was not an attempt to bribe you

425
01:11:21,920 --> 01:11:24,720
only to make your retirement
comfortable

426
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:28,320
How can I be comfortable when my people are in concentration camps?

427
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:31,600
and where is this General who bombs and burns and hangs?

428
01:11:31,680 --> 01:11:33,800
Why has be never come here?

429
01:11:34,040 --> 01:11:36,440
Once he sees this agreement between us

430
01:11:36,480 --> 01:11:38,480
General Gotchiani will be happy to see you

431
01:11:38,520 --> 01:11:44,240
I do not want to see him.
I want to see the last of him

432
01:11:44,680 --> 01:11:50,360
And why is he landing troups?
Where is he going? to the last Oasis?

433
01:11:50,360 --> 01:11:53,040
6000 drums of water

434
01:11:57,280 --> 01:12:02,640
He is going to Kufra

435
01:12:04,960 --> 01:12:10,600
He never wanted peace.
All you wanted was time

436
01:12:12,120 --> 01:12:14,880
We will be with Gotchiani

437
01:12:15,320 --> 01:12:19,320
If you will not come to these terms, I'll promise you immediately terrible war

438
01:12:19,560 --> 01:12:23,360
Oh I know the power of your Government, the power you threatens with...

439
01:12:24,440 --> 01:12:28,960
we've stood against you for 20 years
... and with the help of God

440
01:12:29,400 --> 01:12:34,320
we will stay with you till your end

441
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:39,000
I knew this conclusion would....

442
01:12:53,400 --> 01:12:58,080
poor folks
They think they can ride against the Golden Army

443
01:14:08,520 --> 01:14:11,160
Its Kufra, no question

444
01:14:12,280 --> 01:14:15,200
those soldiers and machines, all going to Kufra

445
01:14:17,000 --> 01:14:21,600
Gotchiani is doing what no one has ever done
he's putting tanks in a desert

446
01:14:22,640 --> 01:14:25,400
The tanks... that is insane

447
01:14:26,280 --> 01:14:33,800
Gotchiani is marching south to Kufra
We, attack North.
We throw him back

448
01:14:34,160 --> 01:14:37,000
We must fight him for Kufra

449
01:14:37,040 --> 01:14:41,480
Sometimes, it is braver not to die. If it is lost, country is not lost

450
01:14:42,360 --> 01:14:44,720
We know your family is there

451
01:14:45,240 --> 01:14:49,080
But, to defend Kufra is to die there

452
01:14:59,840 --> 01:15:02,160
I must go

453
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:07,720
Yes, yes you must

454
01:16:31,880 --> 01:16:34,760
Are you ready to platter them?
Yes sir

455
01:16:36,360 --> 01:16:38,040
Good... We've been given help

456
01:16:39,440 --> 01:16:41,400
Colonel Andriani, open fire

457
01:17:05,680 --> 01:17:07,440
Go now

458
01:19:45,280 --> 01:19:47,200
Fire everything on them

459
01:19:49,680 --> 01:19:51,480
Borm it on their front

460
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:49,440
Murderers

461
01:21:28,120 --> 01:21:32,680
What are you doing?
Consolute Gotchiani's orders

462
01:21:42,840 --> 01:21:46,920
No retreat, we fight and die here

463
01:25:36,640 --> 01:25:39,280
Gentlemen
This is Kufra

464
01:26:26,760 --> 01:26:31,040
